ance in the early Middle Ages, and thence into England. It was a royal name, and its enduring popularity may have been enhanced by the fact that it was borne by a queen of England—  Isabella  (  1296–1358 ), daughter of  Philip IV  of France—even though she led a turbulent life and eventually had her husband,  Edward II , murdered."]},{"name":"Isobel","meanings":["Variant spelling of   Isabel ."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Isabell was born in 1247, in Kingston, Kent, England, United Kingdom. She married Walter de Denne II in 1270, in Kingston, Kent, England. They were the parents of at least 3 sons. She died in 1279, in her hometown, at the age of 32."},"et":{"1247–1279":"1247–1279","1245–1308":"1245–1308","1275–1328":"1275–1328","1278–1346":"1278–1346","1308–Male":"1308–Surnud","1247":"1247","1346":"1346","1279":"1279","1278":"1278","1245":"1245","1275":"1275","1270":"1270","1308":"1308","1328":"1328","Dennehill, Kingston, Kent, England":"Kingston, Kent, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Kingston, Kent, England":"Kingston, Kent, England","Kingstone, Kent, England":"Kingston, Kent, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1247–1279":"1247–1279","1245–1308":"1245–1308","1275–1328":"1275–1328","1278–1346":"1278–1346","1308–Male":"1308–Kuollut","1247":"1247","1346":"1346","1279":"1279","1278":"1278","1245":"1245","1275":"1275","1270":"1270","1308":"1308","1328":"1328","Dennehill, Kingston, Kent, England":"Kingston, Kent, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Kingston, Kent, England":"Kingston, Kent, England","Kingstone, Kent, England":"Kingston, Kent, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"1247–1279":"1247–1279","1245–1308":"1245–1308","1275–1328":"1275–1328","1278–1346":"1278–1346","1308–Male":"1308–Décédé","1247":"1247","1346":"1346","1279":"1279","1278":"1278","1245":"1245","1275":"1275","1270":"1270","1308":"1308","1328":"1328","Dennehill, Kingston, Kent, England":"Kingston, Kent, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","Kingston, Kent, England":"Kingston, Kent, Angleterre","Kingstone, Kent, Eng